                     <p>
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> de <surname>Chyvet</surname>, son
                  of <persName>
                              <forename>Gilbert</forename> de <surname>Fechiston</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, 
                  for himself and his heirs, is bound to the <orgName key="org_103023">hospital of St John of Jerusalem at
                  Newland, co. York</orgName>, in 8d. annual rent, from land in <placeName key="place_103113">Chyvet</placeName>, 
                  of which one toft is called <placeName type="minor">Stokcroft</placeName>, which
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Gillebert</forename>his father</persName> and 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Havisia</forename> his sister</persName> with his 
                  counsel and consent and charter (see the next one, MS. Ch. Yorks. 102) gave to the blessed poor of 
                  the said hospital, in frankalmoigne. 
                     (<origDate notBefore="1240" notAfter="1250" precision="low">c. 1240-50</origDate>.) 
                  . </p>
